pr_body:
## [GSOC'22 Task](https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/wiki/GSoC%2722-Project-List#project-4---circuitverse-simulator-improvements)

Fixes #3161 

### Implemented Tasks

- [x]  Added tests for 
> - [x] AND gate
> - [x] NOR gate
> - [x] NOT gate
> - [x] XNOR gate
> - [x] XOR gate
> - [x] OR gate
> - [x] NAND gate

- [x]  Added workflow to [run tests](https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/runs/6725951966?check_suite_focus=true) on Pull Request(only for the code changes inside simulator/ dir)

## Basics Steps to create a Test are:
1. Setup Simulator Environment using setup() function.
2. Load circuit Data using load() function.
3. Run test using testbench engine (runAll() function).

## Demo 

### All Tests Pass

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76155456/171418413-4e9a209a-6bc5-4933-a842-8281e0f65fee.mov



## Working
![163724136-f7a6b647-2041-4837-a9ea-0ec8b3fda051](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76155456/171417854-f6160085-dffd-4f1f-b8a5-edc2ec07b816.jpeg)

---

### Errors while creating test suite: https://gist.github.com/pulkit-30/9182f6875af1239515e1cc4a481b6f25#file-errors-md

### Npm modules installed: https://gist.github.com/pulkit-30/9182f6875af1239515e1cc4a481b6f25#file-packages-md

pr_title: feat: updated docs for simulator testing
pr_body:
Fixes #3235 

Added instruction to run tests before opening  Pull Request.

Changes:

## Tests

Before making a pull request, it is a good idea to check that all tests are passing locally.

- To run the system tests, run `bundle exec rspec` .
- To run the simulator tests, run `yarn run test` .

**Note:** To pass the system tests, you need the [Chrome Browser](https://www.google.com/chrome/) installed.

pr_title: feat: import and export of circuit files
pr_body:
## [GSOC](https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/wiki/GSoC%2722-Project-List#project-4---circuitverse-simulator-improvements)
 
Fixes #357 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
implemented the import and export of circuit files : A `.cv` extension file that contains the circuit data that can be exported and imported from/to the simulator


### Screenshots of the changes (If any) -

## GSoC'22

Fixes #2931
Fixes #2964 
Fixes #3058 

This PR is for New UI designed For CircuitVerse website Small screen version

Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
Following things are changed for smaller screen
1.Circuit Element (Redesigned)
2.Properties panel (Redesigned)
3.Time Diagram (Redesigned)

Following new things are added in this PR for smaller screen
1.Touch button menu
2.Live button (Fit to screen, Undo, Delete)
3.Quick menu

Fixes #

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -

Tried to toggle Mobile-Ui using javascript

added device detection logic in [ux.js](https://github.com/CircuitVerse/CircuitVerse/pull/3268/files#diff-529f52680d5a10f762be99282855219c6f66bbfe5319c62bf3d6318e24231475) file and then appending style code in head (if mobile view)
